<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-11-15T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-11-15T14:00:00-05:00" n="362" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d362">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">662.116 Autos/14: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Dodd</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-11-15T14:00:00-05:00">November 15, 1934—2
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>130. Your 209, November 6, 5 p.m.<note n="43" xml:id="d362fn43">Not
                                    found in Department files.</note> In view of reported new German
                                restrictions on American automotive imports, the Department requests
                                that you follow the matter carefully and submit a full report as
                                early as practicable indicating whether discrimination is
                                involved.</p>
                            <p>If so, please take steps in the proper quarter to reserve our
                                position.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>